<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Educational Podcast Aggregator</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background: linear-gradient(to right, #f4f4f4, #e0e0e0);
            margin: 0;
            padding: 20px;
        }
        .container {
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            background: #fff;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 15px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
            transition: box-shadow 0.3s ease;
        }
        .container:hover {
            box-shadow: 0 0 25px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
        }
        h1 {
            font-size: 2.5em;
            font-weight: bold;
            color: #333;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }
        p {
            font-size: 1.1em;
            color: #666;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }
        .podcast {
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            padding-bottom: 10px;
            border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;
        }
        .podcast img {
            max-width: 100%;
            height: auto;
            border: 1px solid #ddd;
            border-radius: 4px;
        }
        .podcast h2 {
            font-size: 1.8em;
            font-weight: bold;
            color: #333;
            margin-top: 0;
        }
        .podcast p {
            font-size: 1em;
            color: #444;
            line-height: 1.5;
        }
        .podcast a {
            color: #1a73e8;
            text-decoration: none;
            font-weight: bold;
        }
        .podcast a:hover {
            text-decoration: underline;
        }
        .button-container {
            text-align: center;
            margin-top: 20px;
        }
        .button-container button {
            padding: 10px 20px;
            font-size: 1.1em;
            border: 2px solid #1a73e8;
            border-radius: 4px;
            background: #1a73e8;
            color: white;
            cursor: pointer;
            transition: background 0.3s ease, color 0.3s ease;
        }
        .button-container button:hover {
            background: white;
            color: #1a73e8;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Educational Podcast Aggregator</h1>
        <p>Welcome to the <strong>Educational Podcast Aggregator</strong>! Here you can find some great podcasts to expand your knowledge. We have curated a list of podcasts that cover a variety of topics. Feel free to explore and <em>learn something new every day</em>.</p>
        
        <hr>
        
        <div class="podcast">
            <h2>Learning with Experts</h2>
            <img src="https://tedxwinterpark.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/consejos-sacar-maximo-partido-elearning.jpg" alt="Learning with Experts" width="200">
            <p>This podcast features interviews with top experts in various fields. <a href="https://www.commonsense.org/education/lists/best-podcast-apps-and-websites-for-students" target="_blank">Listen here</a>.</p>
            <span>Category: <strong>Education</strong></span>
        </div>
        
        <div class="podcast">
            <h2>Science Simplified</h2>
            <img src="https://jnvscienceguru.weebly.com/uploads/1/2/5/2/12524655/cartoon-logo_orig.jpg" alt="Science Simplified" width="200">
            <p>Exploring complex science topics in simple terms. <a href="https://hellobio.com/blog/our-top-10-science-podcasts.html" target="_blank">Listen here</a>.</p>
            <span>Category: <strong>Science</strong></span>
        </div>
        
        <div class="podcast">
            <h2>History Uncovered</h2>
            <img src="https://www.mooc.org/hubfs/how-study-history-jpg.jpeg" alt="History Uncovered" width="200">
            <p>In-depth discussions on historical events and figures. <a href="https://www.timeout.com/things-to-do/best-history-podcasts" target="_blank">Listen here</a>.</p>
            <span>Category: <strong>History</strong></span>
        </div>
        
        <div class="button-container">
            <button id="subscribe-button">Subscribe to Newsletter</button>
        </div>
    </div>

    <script>
        // Handle button click
        document.getElementById('subscribe-button').addEventListener('click', function() {
            let userEmail = prompt('Please enter your email address to subscribe:');
            if (userEmail) {
                if (validateEmail(userEmail)) {
                    alert('Thank you for subscribing!');
                } else {
                    alert('Please enter a valid email address.');
                }
            } else {
                alert('Subscription cancelled.');
            }
        });

        function validateEmail(email) {
            // Simple email validation
            const re = /^[^\s@]+@[^\s@]+\.[^\s@]+$/;
            return re.test(String(email).toLowerCase());
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>
